definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + L-proline + tRNA(Pro) -eq- AMP + diphosphate + L-prolyl-tRNA(Pro).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + L-serine + tRNA(Ser) -eq- AMP + diphosphate + L-seryl-tRNA(Ser).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + L-threonine + tRNA(Thr) -eq- AMP + diphosphate + L-threonyl-tRNA(Thr).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + L-tryptophan + tRNA(Trp) -eq- AMP + diphosphate + L-tryptophanyl-tRNA(Trp).
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-tyrosine + ATP + tRNA(Tyr) -eq- L-tyrosyl-tRNA(Tyr) + AMP + diphosphate + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-valine + ATP + tRNA(Val) -eq- L-valyl-tRNA(Val) + AMP + diphosphate + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-tryptophan + O2 -eq- N-formyl-L-kynurenine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-serine + (1S,2R)-1-C-(indol-3-yl)glycerol 3-phosphate -eq- L-tryptophan + glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + detyrosinated alpha-tubulin + L-tyrosine -eq- alpha-tubulin + ADP + phosphate.
Catalysis of the hydroxylation of tyramine to form octopamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-tyrosine -eq- tyramine + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-tyrosine + 2-oxoglutarate -eq- 4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate + L-glutamate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  E1 + ubiquitin + ATP---gt- E1-ubiquitin + AMP + PPi, where the E1-ubiquitin linkage is a thioester bond between the C-terminal glycine of Ub and a sulfhydryl side group of an E1 cysteine residue. This is the first step in a cascade of reactions in which ubiquitin is ultimately added to a protein substrate.
Catalysis of the transfer of ubiquitin from one protein to another via the reaction X-Ub + Y ---gt- Y-Ub + X, where both X-Ub and Y-Ub are covalent linkages.
Catalysis of the thiol-dependent hydrolysis of a peptide bond formed by the C-terminal glycine of ubiquitin.

Catalysis of the cleavage of the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar, releasing a free base and leaving an apyrimidinic (AP) site. Enzymes with this activity recognize and remove uracil bases in DNA that result from the deamination of cytosine or the misincorporation of dUTP opposite an adenine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  diphosphate + UMP -eq- 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate + uracil.
Catalysis of the reaction -  urate + O2 + H2O -eq- 5-hydroxyisourate + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + bicarbonate + urea -eq- ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate + urea-1-carboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-ureidoglycolate + H(2)O + 2 H(+) -eq- CO(2) + glyoxylate + 2 NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + uridine -eq- ADP + UMP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  uridine + phosphate -eq- uracil + alpha-D-ribose 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 S-adenosyl-L-methionine + uroporphyrin III -eq- 2 S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + precorrin-2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  hydroxymethylbilane -eq- H(2)O + uroporphyrinogen III.
Catalysis of the reaction -  uroporphyrinogen-III -eq- coproporphyrinogen + 4 CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  xanthine + NAD+ + H2O -eq- urate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  xanthine + H2O + O2 -eq- urate + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-xylulose + ATP -eq- D-xylulose 5-phosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of an enzyme.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of dUTP pyrophosphatase.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a phospholipase, an enzyme that catalyzes of the hydrolysis of a phospholipid.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a protein kinase, an enzyme which phosphorylates a protein.

label.value: cyclin-dependent protein serine|threonine kinase inhibitor activity

definition.value: Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a cyclin-dependent protein serine|threonine kinase.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a cAMP-dependent protein kinase.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a protein phosphatase, an enzyme that hydrolyzes phosphate groups from phosphorylated proteins.

Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a serine|threonine protein phosphatase, an enzyme that catalyzes the reaction -  protein serine|threonine phosphate + H2O -eq- protein serine|threonine + phosphate.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of an endopeptidase, any enzyme that hydrolyzes nonterminal peptide bonds in polypeptides.

Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of serine-type endopeptidases, enzymes that catalyze the hydrolysis of nonterminal peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain -  a serine residue (and a histidine residue) are at the active center of the enzyme.

Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a cysteine-type endopeptidase, any enzyme that hydrolyzes peptide bonds in polypeptides by a mechanism in which the sulfhydryl group of a cysteine residue at the active center acts as a nucleophile.
Conveys a signal across a cell to trigger a change in cell function or state. A signal is a physical entity or change in state that is used to transfer information in order to trigger a response.
Combining with an extracellular or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell activity.

Receiving an asialoglycoprotein, and delivering the asialoglycoprotein into the cell via endocytosis. An asialoglycoprotein is a plasma glycoproteins from which the terminal sialic acid residue on their complex carbohydrate groups has been removed. The asialoglycoprotein receptor recognizes the terminal galactose and N-acetylgalactosamine units of the asialoglycoprotein, the receptor-ligand complex is internalized and transported to a sorting organelle where disassociation occurs before the receptor is recycled to the cell membrane.

Combining with an aryl hydrocarbon and transmitting the signal to initiate a change in cell activity. The aryl hydrocarbon receptor is a ligand-activated transcription factor which translocates to the nucleus to activate transcription upon ligand-binding.
Combining with any component or product of the complement cascade and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.
Combining with the C3a product of the complement cascade and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.
Combining with the C3b product of the complement cascade and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.
Combining with the C5a product of the complement cascade and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

label.value: ligand-activated sequence-specific DNA binding RNA polymerase II transcription factor activity

definition.value: Combining with a signal and transmitting the signal to the transcriptional machinery by interacting selectively and non-covalently with a specific DNA sequence in order to modulate transcription by RNA polymerase II.

Combining with juvenile hormone and transmitting the signal to the transcriptional machinery by interacting selectively and non-covalently with a specific DNA sequence in order to modulate transcription by RNA polymerase II.

Combining with an androgen and transmitting the signal to the transcriptional machinery by interacting selectively and non-covalently with an androgen response element in DNA in order to modulate transcription by RNA polymerase II.
